("984","231","_elementor_data","[{\"id\":\"553971c9\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5cb2cf3e\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"8f57e56\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>COMIDAS T\\u00cdPICAS<\\/p><p><img class=\\\"size-medium wp-image-179 aligncenter\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/patrimoniocultural.ml\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/batata-300x199.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"199\\\" \\/><\\/p><p>H\\u00e1 ind\\u00edcios de que a batata desembarcou, pelos navegadores espanh\\u00f3is, na Europa por volta de 1550.O delicioso alimento foi amplamente aceito, j\\u00e1 que as na\\u00e7\\u00f5es n\\u00e3o eram capazes de alimentar toda a popula\\u00e7\\u00e3o, e foi muito bem recebido na Irlanda, tornando-se parte dos principais pratos tradicionais.<\\/p><p>Al\\u00e9m das lendas e hist\\u00f3rias h\\u00e1 um fato importante, a batata foi o principal alimento irland\\u00eas durante alguns s\\u00e9culos, para se ter uma no\\u00e7\\u00e3o: um adulto chegava a consumir mais de 6kg de batata por dia!<br \\/>Agora vamos aos pratos:<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Crisps Sandwich<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><img class=\\\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-218\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/patrimoniocultural.ml\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/WhatsApp-Image-2018-10-23-at-18.43.25-1-300x185.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"185\\\" \\/><\\/p><p>Simples, por\\u00e9m gostoso, o lanche \\u00e9 feito de duas fatias de p\\u00e3o recheadas de batatas chips e manteiga.<\\/p><p>Obs: uma marca de batatas chips reconhecida na Irlanda \\u00e9 a Tayto<\\/p><p><img class=\\\"size-medium wp-image-219 aligncenter\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/patrimoniocultural.ml\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/WhatsApp-Image-2018-10-23-at-18.43.25-300x300.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"300\\\" \\/><\\/p><p>\\u2022 Caf\\u00e9 da manh\\u00e3 irland\\u00eas (irish breakfast)<\\/p><p><img class=\\\"size-medium wp-image-217 aligncenter\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/patrimoniocultural.ml\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/WhatsApp-Image-2018-10-23-at-18.43.26-300x201.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"201\\\" \\/><\\/p><p>O caf\\u00e9 da manh\\u00e3 irland\\u00eas \\u00e9 bem diferente do nosso e tamb\\u00e9m \\u00e9 pesado, composto por bacon, p\\u00e3o de forma, ovo, lingui\\u00e7as, cogumelos, tomate, batatas e feij\\u00e3o, acompanhado com uma xicara de caf\\u00e9, ou ch\\u00e1.<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Irish Stew<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><img class=\\\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-226\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/patrimoniocultural.ml\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/WhatsApp-Image-2018-10-23-at-18.43.26-5-300x227.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"227\\\" \\/><\\/p><p>O Irish Stew \\u00e9 um guisado t\\u00edpico irland\\u00eas com carne, batatas (\\u00e9 claro!), cenoura, alho-por\\u00f3, couve branca e aipo. Parece delicioso, n\\u00e3o parece?<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Chicken roll ou Breakfast roll<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><img class=\\\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-221\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/patrimoniocultural.ml\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/WhatsApp-Image-2018-10-23-at-18.43.26-2-300x225.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"225\\\" \\/><\\/p><p>O Chicken roll ou Breakfast roll tem essas duas vers\\u00f5es, a primeira com p\\u00e3o baguette, frango empanado, alface e manteiga ou maionese. O segundo com p\\u00e3o baguette e os ingredientes do Irish Breakfast.<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Shepherd\\u2019s pie<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><img class=\\\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-222\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/patrimoniocultural.ml\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/WhatsApp-Image-2018-10-23-at-18.43.26-3-300x200.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"200\\\" \\/><\\/p><p>O shepherd\\u2019pie (torta do pastor) \\u00e9 uma torta de carne, tamb\\u00e9m incrementada com legumes, coberta por pur\\u00ea de batata e assada no forno.<\\/p><p>BEBIDAS<\\/p><p>Agora vamos \\u00e0s bebidas mais conhecidas na Irlanda:<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Cerveja Guinness<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><img class=\\\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-223\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/patrimoniocultural.ml\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/WhatsApp-Image-2018-10-23-at-18.43.26-4-300x150.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"150\\\" \\/><\\/p><p>A cerveja Guiness, criada por Arthur Guinness em 1759, \\u00e9 uma cerveja escura e, dito por muitos, com um sabor incompar\\u00e1vel.<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Irish coffee<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><img class=\\\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-224\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/patrimoniocultural.ml\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/WhatsApp-Image-2018-10-23-at-18.43.27-300x200.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"300\\\" height=\\\"200\\\" \\/><\\/p><p>Pode parecer um caf\\u00e9 comum, mas n\\u00e3o \\u00e9. O irish coffee, al\\u00e9m de caf\\u00e9, tem uma dose de u\\u00edsque, a\\u00e7\\u00facar e chantilly.<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Baileys<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><img class=\\\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-225\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/patrimoniocultural.ml\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/WhatsApp-Image-2018-10-23-at-18.43.27-1-225x300.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"225\\\" height=\\\"300\\\" \\/><\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\">\\u00c9 o original creme de licor irland\\u00eas, pode ser servido em coquet\\u00e9is ou somente com cubos de gelo.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"79a4ea9\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"57529dd\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"126f306\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"tax_query\":[\"category:tradicoes-irlandesas\",\"category:historia-irlandesa\",\"category:musicas-irlanda\"],\"posts_per_page\":3,\"display_summary\":\"\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"lae-posts-carousel\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]"),
